BUSINESS REQUIREMENT

Every day, insurance companies handle thousands of claims. Many of these claims are fraudulent, 
meaning that people purposefully give inaccurate or inflated information in order to profit financially.
Insurance companies suffer significant financial losses as a result of fraudulent claims, which also raise operating expenses.
Conventional fraud detection techniques mostly rely on rule-based systems and manual investigation, 
which are frequently costly, time-consuming, and less successful at spotting intricate fraud patterns.
As a result, an intelligent system that can automatically evaluate insurance claim data 
and precisely and effectively detect possible fraudulent claims is required.
